  "suggestion": "[cognitive-psychology+psychometrics+domain-adaptation] REFINEMENT — Domain-Specific Prediction Templates. The active inference engine generates plausible but domain-agnostic outputs. Add a lookup of 8 domain reasoning templates, one per benchmark domain: cognitive-bias uses heuristic-override logic (identify the relevant bias, apply its mechanism), emotion uses valence+arousal circumplex path, social uses norm-violation detection, decision uses prospect theory framing (gains vs losses, reference points), development uses stage-gating (Piaget/Erikson), personality uses Big Five trait activation, psychopathology uses symptom-cluster matching, motivation uses SDT need-satisfaction (autonomy/competence/relatedness). Implementation: before calling the active inference engine, route through the domain template to pre-structure the output schema. This makes predictions concrete enough for semantic matching to score them. — Math: P(response | situation, domain) = P(response | template(domain)) * P(situation | response) / Z — domain templates act as structured priors; [allostasis+homeostasis+hierarchy-of-needs+affective-neuroscience+control-theory] Multi-Level Homeostatic Regulation (Allostasis Engine). Replace the single free-energy minimizer with a stack of set-points at 4 levels: (1) safety/threat — immediate physical/social danger, (2) resource/energy — effort/reward balance, (3) social standing — belonging, status, fairness, (4) meaning/coherence — narrative identity. At each moment, compute deviation from set-point at every level. The level with MAXIMUM deviation drives behavior. Response = regulatory action that most efficiently restores the most violated level. Emotion = signal of which level is violated and by how much (fear = safety deficit, shame = standing deficit, confusion = coherence deficit, exhaustion = resource deficit). This explains why hunger overrides social goals, and why existential crisis overrides hunger. — Math: argmax_behavior sum_level [ w_level * deviation_level(behavior) ], where deviation = |current - setpoint| and w_level = urgency weight (safety >> social >> meaning); [music-theory+cognitive-dissonance+vector-semantics+topology+Gestalt-psychology] Cognitive Consonance Engine (Music Theory cross-pollination). Model the mind as a chord progression: beliefs are notes, and their combination either consonates (mutually reinforcing expectations) or dissonates (conflicting predictions). Cognitive dissonance is literally harmonic dissonance — the system must resolve it. Response behavior is the resolution move (change belief, change behavior, add rationalizing belief). Emotion is the affective texture of the current chord: consonant chords = calm/confident, dissonant = anxious/motivated-to-change, unresolved dissonance = rumination/OCD. Implementation: represent active beliefs as a small set of vectors, measure pairwise cosine similarity — high similarity = consonance, low/negative = dissonance. Behavior prediction: if dissonance > threshold, predict dissonance-reduction response (rationalization, avoidance, change). — Math: dissonance(beliefs) = 1 - mean(cosine_sim(b_i, b_j) for all pairs i≠j). Resolution_pressure = max(0, dissonance - tolerance_threshold). Behavior = argmin_action dissonance(beliefs after action)",
